apologize /əˈpɒləˌdʒaɪz/

(apologizing,apologized,apologizes) BRIT also  apologise 

1. V-I When you apologize to someone, you say that you are sorry that you have hurt them or caused trouble for them. You can say ' I apologize ' as a formal way of saying sorry. 表达歉意 

例： I apologize for being late, but I have just had a message from the hospital. 我为迟到表示歉意，但我刚得到了来自医院的一个消息。 

例： He apologized to the people who had been affected. 他向受到了影响的人道了歉。

